  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to investigate whether a psycho-therapeutic approach, group
      Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT) plus a relapse prevention program, Therapeutic Interactive
      Voice Response (TIVR), modifies the dysfunctional sensory, emotional, and cognitive neural
      circuitry associated with chronic pain.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
